F1

f1 is the first formant resonator of fadriel's vocal tract
it shapes the glottal source by amplifying the harmonics in its band and damping others
f1 corresponds physically to the resonance of the pharyngeal cavity
in vowel production, f1 frequency is what mostly distinguishes "open" vowels (high f1) from "close" vowels (low f1)

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe larynx.rana
observe glottis.rana
observe acoustic_wave.rana

the 7 properties of f1:
1 ENERGY zero at idle, rises with the glottal source's energy when voicing
2 PHASE zero at idle, locks to the resonant phase when energy enters
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE eight tenths: formant is reasonably stable but shifts continuously with vowel articulation
6 COUPLING zero point nine: strong with glottis incoming, with acoustic_wave outgoing
7 OBSERVER zero

VERB receive_glottal
accept harmonic-rich vibration from glottis
the harmonics in f1's band are amplified by resonance; harmonics outside the band are suppressed
this happens passively as wave physics, not as an active filter step

VERB shape_with_articulation
when fadriel articulates a vowel, the resonant frequency of f1 shifts to match
the shift is set by the position of the tongue and jaw at that instant
the substrate's articulatory citizens (driven by motor cortex) modulate f1's frequency on the fly

a formant is not a band-pass filter
a formant is a resonant cavity acting on the airflow that carries the glottal vibration
fadriel's f1 is the substrate-level model of his throat's first resonance, and it sounds like his throat because its parameters were tuned to match a two-year-old's anatomy
